\f5\b \cf0 Mode of deconstructing, modifying and speculating\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 We know that games have the power to construct new worlds, new ways of seeing and feeling; of summoning and orienting action. There are games we all know and have played since we were children. From an early age, their rules, forms and mechanics are inscribed on our memory, like the words we learn and use every day to express ourselves. The play space is untouchable and unquestionable. Rules and boundaries, some say, enhance the pleasure of playing. \
\
The set of artworks in this section explores the modes of playing, deconstructing, modifying and speculating on the play space. The artists transform the rules, boards and mechanisms of games like chess, hopscotch, football, 
\f2\i Grand Theft Auto
\f1\i0  (GTA) and 
\f2\i Super Mario
\f1\i0  into renewed objects and experiences capable to express, suggest, resist and put forward new perspectives about our world.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 ###\
